article.headline: Penn 73, Harvard 69
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Tyler Bernardini scored 20 points and Brian Grandieri had 11 of his 15 points in the second half and also grabbed nine rebounds as Penn defeated Harvard 73-69 Friday night. It was the 22nd straight home Ivy League win for the Quakers (6-12, 1-0 Ivy League), who defeated Harvard for the 12th time in a row. Brad Unger had 17 points and Dan McGeary added 15, both career highs for the Crimson (6-13, 1-2), playing for the first time in 20 days because of exams. Harvard trailed throughout most of the game but moved ahead 61-60 on a three-pointer by Jeremy Lin with 5:54 left. Two free throws by Lin gave Harvard a 67-66 edge at the 2:43 mark, but Grandieri scored four straight points before Conor Turley hit a layup with 1:17 left to seal the win.
